        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>Sept 16<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1862</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>31 Nassau St.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>I. Leeser Esq.</addressee>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your letter of yesterday<lb/> is at hand. Enclosed find $2.62, <hi
                    rend="underline">large</hi><lb/> amount of <persName>Mr Loewe's</persName>
                indebtedness.</p>
            <p>When I first wrote you I was under the<lb/> impression that <persName>Mr
                    Loewe</persName> owed you<lb/> a balance, independent of the advertisement<lb/>
                last inserted. Your receipted bill being<lb/> only for the latter, of course
                satisfies me to<lb/> the contrary. Your commission to <persName>Mr<lb/>
                    Isaacs</persName> with your regards to <persName>Mr Loewe</persName> will<lb/>
                both be attended to.</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Yours Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Joseph H. Levy</persName>.</p>
